  "poem": {
    "content": "The sea drifts, a canvas gray,\nUnable to borrow a smile today.\nA run for peace, a frantic ride,\nFrom the shore of the moral divide.\n\nTheory whispered, a salty trace,\nBiology bending to time and space.\nAn assault of thought, a crashing wave,\nAs title and self, the ocean gave.\n\nThe heart seeks solace, a gentle hand,\nTo boost the spirit, across the land.\nYet echoes copy, a hollow sound,\nWhere truth is lost, and can't be found.\n\nHope's frail vessel, caught in the storm,\nUnable to navigate, keep safe and warm.\nIs there a safe place to alight?\nOr will the darkness steal the light?",
